Sla1 patch density in Ede1âˆ†PQCC-Syp1 fusion

Last compiled on March 21, 2022

Experiment

The aim of the experiment is to determine Sla1 patch density where the central region deletion (PQ-rich and coiled-coil) of Ede1 is attached to Syp1 using the FRB-FKBP system.

Imaging

All images were captured with the halide lamp @ 50% power using the GFP filter cube and 400 ms exposure per slice. 5 micron stacks were taken with 0.2 micron step.

List of strains used

Strain Mutations
MKY0140 wild type
MKY0654 ede1âˆ†
MKY4343 Ede1âˆ†(366-900)-mCherry-FKBP, SYP1-FRB, fpr1âˆ†, tor1-1

All: Sla1-EGFP

MKY4343 was cultured with 10 ug/ml rapamycin (+R) or equivalent volume of solvent (1% DMSO in culture, -R).

Image processing

Patch numbers were extracted with a custom Python script site_counter.py (part of package impromptu called mkimage) using functions from the scikit-image package. Briefly, the images were median-filter subtracted with a 5 px disk brush and thresholded using the Yen method. The thresholded image was eroded using the number of non-zero neighbouring pixels in 3D as the erosion criterion. The spots were counted using skimage.measure.label() function with 2-connectivity.

Cross-section area was obtained by median-filtering of the stack with 10px disk brush, calculating the maximum projection image, thresholding using Otsuâ€™s algorithm and using skimage.measure.regionprops() to obtain area. Note that these are pixel counts of cross-section area. To determine the total surface area, I assume that an unbudded cell is spherical (suface area is four times the cross-section area).

This call to site_counter was used to process all datasets:

process_folder(path, median_radius = 5, erosion_n = 1, con = 2,
                   method = Yen, mask = False, loop = False, save_images = True)

data_cleanup.Rmd was used to gather all output into tidy data frames with no further modifications.

Statistical summary

Sla1 density

Per dataset

We measured the number of patches and cell surface area. We can combine these these as \(density = \frac{patches}{area}\), calculated for each cell individually.

Hypothesis testing

Are the Ede1 groups significantly different?

We will use a linear model of density_mean ~ ede1 to perform an ANOVA test on replicate-level means, followed by a Tukey test for multiple comparisons.

Plots

SuperPlots

SuperPlots with significance

Letâ€™s add significance stars based on Tukeyâ€™s test.

Letter annotations

In this view, groups sharing at least one letter are not significant at a chosen \(\alpha\) (here, 5%).

Pros:

  • less cluttered
  • simpler to read and edit

Cons:

  • cannot distinguish different confidence levels
  • focus on non-findings
